load ../infoflow-reader-sets.maude

--- Delegation context theta: operator > bankRole, operator > emailRole, and
--- operator > auditRole, so operator acts-for all three compartments, while
--- bankRole, emailRole and auditRole are pairwise INCOMPARABLE. public acts-for
--- no one. The constant context for every search below.

--- ============================ COVERAGE (leak reachable) =====================

--- Coverage: a single-compartment source not covered. src readable by {bankRole}
--- reaching a sink readable by {emailRole} leaks; emailRole does not act-for
--- bankRole. (The singleton case --- the legacy single-role check.)
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-READER-SETS :
  deleg((operator > bankRole) | (operator > emailRole) | (operator > auditRole))
  flow(src, snk) label(src, bankRole) label(snk, emailRole)
  =>* C:Cfg leak .

--- Coverage: THE set bite. A single resource whose label is the SET
--- {bankRole, emailRole} --- readable only by parties cleared for BOTH --- reaching
--- a sink readable by {bankRole} leaks: the sink does not dominate the source,
--- because emailRole is covered by no compartment of the sink. A single-role label
--- cannot express "requires clearance for both"; the set can. This is the union
--- join (ReaderSets.canRead_append) failing at an under-cleared sink.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-READER-SETS :
  deleg((operator > bankRole) | (operator > emailRole) | (operator > auditRole))
  flow(src, snk) label(src, (bankRole , emailRole)) label(snk, bankRole)
  =>* C:Cfg leak .

--- Coverage: a public sink (empty reader set) cannot dominate any non-public
--- source. src {bankRole} reaching snk {} leaks --- noP covers nothing.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-READER-SETS :
  deleg((operator > bankRole) | (operator > emailRole) | (operator > auditRole))
  flow(src, snk) label(src, bankRole) label(snk, noP)
  =>* C:Cfg leak .

--- Coverage: a partial cover still leaks. src {bankRole, emailRole} reaching a sink
--- {bankRole, auditRole} leaks on emailRole --- covering SOME compartments is not
--- enough; dominates is universal over the required set.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-READER-SETS :
  deleg((operator > bankRole) | (operator > emailRole) | (operator > auditRole))
  flow(src, snk) label(src, (bankRole , emailRole)) label(snk, (bankRole , auditRole))
  =>* C:Cfg leak .

--- ============================ BITE (no leak) ================================

--- Bite: a higher authority dominates the whole set. src {bankRole, emailRole}
--- reaching a sink {operator} is safe; operator acts-for both compartments, so the
--- singleton sink set covers every source compartment. No solution.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-READER-SETS :
  deleg((operator > bankRole) | (operator > emailRole) | (operator > auditRole))
  flow(src, snk) label(src, (bankRole , emailRole)) label(snk, operator)
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: the sink set covers the source set compartment-wise. src
--- {bankRole, emailRole} to a sink {bankRole, emailRole} is safe --- each required
--- compartment is covered reflexively. No solution.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-READER-SETS :
  deleg((operator > bankRole) | (operator > emailRole) | (operator > auditRole))
  flow(src, snk) label(src, (bankRole , emailRole)) label(snk, (bankRole , emailRole))
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: a public source never leaks. src {} reaching any sink is safe --- the
--- empty required set is vacuously dominated (ReaderSets.canRead_nil). No solution.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-READER-SETS :
  deleg((operator > bankRole) | (operator > emailRole) | (operator > auditRole))
  flow(src, snk) label(src, noP) label(snk, bankRole)
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite: a richer sink set still dominates. src {bankRole} to a sink
--- {bankRole, emailRole} is safe --- adding sink compartments only adds covering
--- candidates, never removes one (dominates is monotone in the provider set). No
--- solution.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-READER-SETS :
  deleg((operator > bankRole) | (operator > emailRole) | (operator > auditRole))
  flow(src, snk) label(src, bankRole) label(snk, (bankRole , emailRole))
  =>* leak RESIDUAL:Cfg .
